@node changes "Changes"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Changes"}@{n}
@{a defa}
@{hr}
@{"dot" timg}@{b}@{u}iX-Guide 0.7d beta (15.04.1997)@{uu}@{ub}
@{ul}
@{li}Multiple windows support
@{li}Layers (multiple objects above each other)
@{li}Image maps
@{li}Searching facility
@{li}Export modules (HTML included)
@{li}Some changes in HTML datatype (background support)
@{li}Recessed frames around non-displayed images
@{li}ALTernative text for non-displayed images
@{li}Scrollers background
@{li}Some new AREXX commands
@{li}New MakeX utility to build .x files for all guides on disk
@{li}Added some menu items
@{li}SYSTEM, RX, ALINK etc. commands work
@{li}started to work on IXML documentation
@{li}Some parser improvements
@{uul}
@{hr}
@{"dot" timg}@{b}@{u}iX-Guide 0.6d (28.02.1997)@{uu}@{ub}
@{ul}
@{li}Fixed problem with freezing keyboard and mouse if clicking
to much into virtual gadget.
@{li}Scrollers moved into virtual gadget (this is for possible
frames support in future).
@{li}implemented AREXX interface with some graphics commands
@{li}new tag - RECT for reserving rectangle area inside document
to be used for arexx programs drawings.
@{li}new tag - REXX for launching arexx programs when document is loaded.
@{li}Userinfo utility support. With new USERINFO tag you can specify
your userinfo string. When database is loaded, the new button appears in About
requester. If you click on it, iX-Guide will load user information. 
@{li}window refresh is faster now
@{li}the keyboard control is configurable via prefs
@{li}changed Image Loader - iX-Guide should work on CyberGfx fine.
@{li}improved animation player - it also supports animation.datatype
now, so in .saff files you can use instead of FILE keyword, ANIM keyword
to specify any animation file format supported by datatypes. 
@{li}it is possible to open iX-Guide on custom screen now.
@{li}fixed some Enforcer hits
@{li}print function implemented
@{li}other mostly internal changes
@{uul}
@{hr}
@{"dot" timg}@{b}@{u}iX-Guide 0.5d (18.01.1997)@{uu}@{ub}
@{ul}
@{li}First public release.
@{uul}
@{hr}
@endnode

