@node introduction "Introduction"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Introduction"}@{n}
@{a defa}

Now some table test !@{p}

@{cl}
@{> B1 F R}The idea of @{_ix} was to give user nice and attractive documents
with lots of multimedia elements but at the same time a minimal hardware
and software requirements.
 I don't know if I succeded in that minimal
requirements because @{_ix} can sometimes eat a lot of memory@{<}
@{> B5 F}and also it can be slow with large, complicated documents but that is normal
when you are working with lots of graphics. And if you compare requirements
with requirements of HTML browsers then it's not so bad.@{p}
@{_ix} is IXML (@{" iX Markup Language " LINK ixml10.ixml/main})
viewer. @{b}IXML@{ub} is actually the extension of @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub}@{<}
@{ucl}
    
hypertext markup language. Since it is based on @{b}AmigaGuide,@{ub} @{b}IXML@{ub}
is @{" compatible " LINK agcomp} with old @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub} documents.
I also added to @{_ix} new feature which makes @{_ix}
universal viewer. That new feature is @{" iX Datatype system " LINK ixdt.ixml/main}
which makes it possible to view other file formats with @{_ix} like HTML
for example. Inside @{_ix} stays @{b}IXML@{ub} viewer, datatypes are
used just to translate other format to @{b}IXML.@{ub}@{p}
@{b}IXML@{ub} has many new tags for better document's look.
Just to mention some of them : Inline images (which can be transparent),
background images (or color), inline animations, text & image alignement,
text coloring, multiple fonts etc.@{p}
Ok, this is some general information about @{_ix}. Push retrace
button to go back to main page or see @{" GUI help " LINK panelbuttons} if
you don't know where is the retrace button.
@endnode

@node usage "Usage"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Usage"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
I think @{_ix} is very simple to use but anyway here is the
small description of GUI elements and keyboard usage.@{p}
@{b}@{u}iX-Guide window@{uu}@{ub}@{n}
@{_ix} window can be resized and every time it is resized, @{_ix}
rebuilds document to match the current dimensions.
At the window title bar you can see something like this:@{n}
@{font deff}[ 1/iX-Guide.ixml ] - Usage@{font ix}@{n}
Number <1> indicates number of this window. <iX-Guide.ixml> is the name
of current database. It is the name specified with @DATABASE tag.
<Usage> is the title of currently displayed node. That name is given
by @NODE or @TITLE tag.@{p}
At the top of window there are @{"panel buttons" LINK panelbuttons}.
When running on screen with non-proportional resolution (e.g. 640x256)
@{_ix} uses halve height images for panel buttons, otherwise it
uses normal proportional images.
Panel buttons also have @{"keyboard shortcuts" LINK keyboard}. Below them is
the biggest part of the window, a scrollable area with displayed
document in it. It is called @{b}virtual gadget@{ub}. You can control
scrolling and input of virtual gadget with mouse or @{"keyboard" LINK keyboard}.
At the bottom of window there are three gadgets. Starting from the left
there is a @{b}load gadget@{ub} which shows loading of document or database or something else.
While the database is loading (building index) the numbers represent bytes but while
building document the numbers are some internal @{_ix} units (entries).
The second gadget is the @{b}image cache gadget@{ub} which shows the current
image cache usage (this cache is in FAST RAM if available). Images that are
in this cache are not currently displayed. Numbers represent current and maximum
cache size in Kbytes. Third gadget is the @{b}status gadget@{ub} which displays
@{_ix} version if nothing is happening, otherwise it shows what @{_ix} is
currently doing.@{p}
Also, many functions are available from @{" menus " LINK menus}
@endnode

@node requirements "Requirements"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Requirements"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{ul}
@{li}AmigaOS 3.0+
@{li}1 Meg of RAM
@{li}appropriate picture datatypes (IFF,GIF,JFIF...)
@{li}020+ recomended
@{li}reqtools.library V37
@{uul}
@endnode

@node agcomp "AmigaGuide compatibility"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "AmigaGuide compatibility"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{b}@{font deff}NOTE : Some tags not listed below are supported but
not yet implemented. They will be available in future releases.@{font ix}@{p}
AmigaGuide tags which are not supported by @{b}IXML@{ub}:
@{ul}
@{li}@{b}Global & Node tags@{ub}
@{ul}
@{li}DNODE@{d}-dynamic node (For iX-Guide same as @NODE)
@{li}ONOPEN@{d}-arexx script to execute when document is opened
@{li}ONCLOSE@{d}-arexx script to execute when document is closed
@{li}SMARTWRAP@{d}-better wordwrapping algorithm (like @IXF in IXML)
@{uul}
@{li}@{b}Attribute tags@{ub}
@{ul}
@{li}ALINK@{d}-open link in new window
@{li}RXS@{d}-execute an arexx string file
@{li}BODY@{d}-restore default formatting for normal body text
@{li}LINDENT@{d}-specify an indent in spaces for the body of paragraph
@{li}PARD@{d}-default paragraph settings
@{li}PARI@{d}-indent in spaces for the first line of paragraph
@{li}PLAIN@{d}-turns off all style attributes
@{li}SETTABS@{d}-specify a series of tab stops in spaces
@{li}TAB@{d}-Outputs a real tab character
@{uul}
@{uul}
@endnode

@node prefs "Preferences"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "iX-Guide prefs"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
On startup @{_ix} reads an ascii file @{b}"ixg.prefs"@{ub} which
must be in the same drawer as @{_ix} program. If file wasn't found
@{_ix} uses the default settings. For any keyword that wasn't found
@{_ix} uses default values. You can edit that file with any text editor.
The file is built up of lines. Semicolon ( @{font deff}@{b};@{ub}@{font ix} ) is used for comment.
Everything in the line after that character will be ignored.
Every line has the following structure:@{n}
@{font deff}<KEYWORD> <ATTRIBUTE 1> [ATTRIBUTE 2] [ATTRIBUTE 3] ...@{font ix}
@{n}
@{hr %90}
@{a c dw}
@{font f4}@{b}@{u}Keywords@{uu}@{ub}@{n}
@{font f3}@{red}Fonts@{tcol}@{n}@{a defa}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}FONT0, FONT1, ... , FONT6@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify fonts and font sizes to be used for F0-F6 font tag attributes.
These fonts can be proportional or fixed width. First attr. is font name
with .font extension and second is font size@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}FWFONT0, FWFONT1, ... , FWFONT6@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify fonts and font sizes to be used for X0-X6 font tag attributes.
These fonts should be fixed width. First attr. is font name
with .font extension and second is font size@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}DEFF@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify font name and font size to be used for DEFF font tag attribute.
This font should be fixed width. If database doesn't have @IXF global tag
which usually means it is old AmigaGuide database this font is used like
default font. First attr. is font name with .font extension and second is font size@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}IXFONT@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify font name and font size to be used for IX font tag attribute.
If database has @IXF global tag which usually means it is IXML database
this font is used like default font. First attr. is font name with .font
extension and second is font size@{p}
@{a c dw}@{font f3}@{red}Button design@{tcol}@{n}@{a defa}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}IBBORTYPE@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Type of border around image button. Attribute can be @{b}none@{ub} (no border),
@{b}single@{ub} (border depth is 1 pixel), or @{b}double@{ub} (border depth
is 2 pixels).@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}TBBORTYPE@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Type of border around text button. For attributes see IBBORTYPE keyword above.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}IBBORCOL@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify colors of border around image button. Four numeric attributes are
required : first number is pen number to use for drawing shine inner edge
of border, second number is pen number to use for drawing shadow inner edge,
third is for shine outer edge and fourth for shadow outer edge. If border type
is single only inner edges are drawn.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}TBBORCOL@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify colors of border around text button. For attributes se IBBORCOL keyword above.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}TBTFG@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Pen number to use for text foreground of text button. Attribute is
pen number.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}TBTBG@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Pen number to use for text background of text button. Attribute is
pen number.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}TBJAM2@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Jam 2 colors when writing text of text button. Attribute can be
@{b}yes@{ub} or @{b}no@{ub}. If 'yes', background color (TBTBG) will be
used when writing text. If 'no', document background will shine through
parts of button.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}TBSTYLE@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Style of text button text. Attribute is one number. Number @{b}0@{ub} is normal
style, @{b}1@{ub} is underlined, @{b}2@{ub} is bold, @{b}4@{ub} is italic.
If you want e.g. @{b}bold and italic@{ub} the number would be @{b}5@{ub} (1+4).@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}IBBORCOL-S, TBBORCOL-S, TBTFG-S, TBTBG-S@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Same as IBBORCOL, TBBORCOL, TBTFG and TBTFG but for selected button.
(See above).@{p}
@{a c dw}@{font f3}@{red}Paths@{tcol}@{n}@{a defa}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}XXRPATH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify path of drawer to store .x (guide index) files in.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}IMGPATH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify path of drawer with system images.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}MODPATH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify path of drawer with .ixm (iXG module) executables.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}DTPATH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify path of drawer with .ixdt (iX Datatype) libraries.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}RXPATH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify path of drawer with .rexx programs@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}UIPATH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify path of drawer where your userinfo utility is installed.@{p}
@{a c dw}@{font f3}@{red}Keyboard@{tcol}@{n}@{a defa}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}LSCROLLSMALL, RSCROLLSMALL, USCROLLSMALL, DSCROLLSMALL@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- specify the keys to be used for scrolling of virtual gadget for small amount
(Left/Right/Up/Down). Default keys are cursor keys.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}LSCROLLBIG, RSCROLLBIG, USCROLLBIG, DSCROLLBIG@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- specify the keys to be used for scrolling of virtual gadget for bigger amount.
Default keys are ALT + cursor keys.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}LSCROLLPAGE, RSCROLLPAGE, USCROLLPAGE, DSCROLLPAGE@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- specify the keys to be used for scrolling of virtual gadget for one page
left/right/up/down.
Default keys are SHIFT + cursor keys.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}LSCROLLTOTAL, RSCROLLTOTAL, USCROLLTOTAL, DSCROLLTOTAL@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- specify the keys to be used for scrolling of virtual gadget at extreme
left/right/top/bottom of document.
Default keys are CTRL + cursor keys.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}INDEX, CONTENTS, RETRACE, FORWARD, BROWSEL, BROWSER,
HELP@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- specify the keys to be used for going to index page, for going to
contents page, for going one page backward in history list, for going one
page forward in history list (NOTE: this is not yet available), for going
to previous node, for going to next node, for going to help page.@{p}
@{a c dw}@{font f3}@{red}Miscellaneous@{tcol}@{n}@{a defa}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}DEFVS@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Default vertical spacing between document lines. Attribute is number
of pixels to use for vertical spacing.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}ICSIZE@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Upper limit of FAST image cache (this cache is in fast ram if available
and all images that are loaded but not displayed are in this cache).
Attribute is upper limit in bytes.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}RBSIZE@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Upper limit of retrace buffer. This buffer is used for document history
(only document name, line position etc.). Attribute is upper limit in bytes.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}SCROLLBS@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Amount of scroll when scrolling with ALT + CURSOR KEYS. The attribute is
amount in pixels.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}SCROLLSS@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Amount of scroll when scrolling with CURSOR KEYS. The attribute is
amount in pixels.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}SCROLLAS@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Amount of scroll when scrolling with arrows in the right bottom corner
of window. The attribute is amount in pixels.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}XINXXR@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Put .x (guide index) files in one drawer (specified with XXRPATH keyword)?
Attribute can be @{b}yes@{ub} or @{b}no@{ub}. If 'yes', iX-Guide will use
one drawer (XXR) for .x files. Otherwise, .x files will be in their documents'
drawer.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}DELAYIL@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Load inlined images ? If attribute is 'no', images will be loaded, if 'yes',
image loading will be delayed.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}INITWD@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Initial window dimensions. Four attributes are required : First number is
@{b}Left@{ub} window position, second is @{b}Top@{ub} window position,
third is window @{b}Width@{ub} and fourth is window @{b}Heigth@{ub}.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}AUTOSB@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Automatically save bookmarks on exit ?. If 'yes' bookmarks will be saved
on exit, otherwise not.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}ILUS@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Update document on every <ILUS> bytes of graphics loaded. Attribute is the number
which represents bytes. If you specify e.g ILUS 60000, document will be
updated on every 60000 bytes of graphics loaded.@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}PLAYANIMS@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Play animations ? @{b}yes@{ub} or @{b}no@{ub}@{p}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}DRAWBG@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Draw background of document ? @{b}yes@{ub} or @{b}no@{ub}@{n}
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}PROPWIDTH@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify the width of vertical scroller in pixels
@{font f2}@{b}@{u}PROPHEIGHT@{uu}@{ub}@{font ix}
- Specify the height of horizontal scroller in pixels
@endnode

@node bugs "Bugs & Problems"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Bugs & Problems"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
On this page I will mention some bugs and problems in @{_ix} I know.
I probably know some more bugs but I can't remember now what were they.@{p}
@{ul}
@{li}Many bugs with multiline objects (alignement, borders...).
@{li}iXG is probably not very stable at low memory conditions.
@{li}If you specify somewhere in your document e.g. LINK to example#iXG,
iX-Guide will jump to the correct line with 'iXG' string but when some image
is loaded above that line, the position of document may be changed.
@{li}When starting iXG from CLI, if you specify NODE and/or LINE to jump to,
iXG may not jump to node specified.
@{uul}
@endnode

@node restrictions "Restrictions"
@toc main
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Restrictions of this version"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
This version of @{_ix} is just the demo so it has many things uncompleted
and not yet implemented. Here is the list of some restrictions of this version.
@{ul}
@{li}Animation object cannot be a link and it cannot be inside multiline object.
@{li}RX, SYSTEM and similar tags are not yet implemented.
@{li}Some menu items do not work yet.
@{li}Also, some window buttons have no effect yet.
@{li}Tab/Shift-Tab cycling not yet implemented.
@{li}BODY tag for global text color, style etc. not yet implemented.
@{li}IB, UIB, WIDTH & HEIGHT tags not yet available.
@{li}No bookmarks yet.
@{uul}@{n}etc.
@endnode

@node panelbuttons "Panel buttons"
@toc usage
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "GUI / Panel buttons"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{b}Panel buttons@{ub} are placed at the top of the window between window title bar
and document area. These images are placed in a 'sysimg' drawer as a 'buttons.picture'.
You can change them by editing that picture in some paint program.@{n}
Here are the descriptions of each button going from left to right:@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}INFO@{us}@{ub} - press this button to obtain some information
about @{_ix} and current database.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}LOAD NEW FILE@{us}@{ub} - This will open the file requester. Choose
the appropriate file and press OK to load file or cancel to abort the action.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}OPEN NEW WINDOW@{us}@{ub} - Not available@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}INDEX@{us}@{ub} - This will bring you the index document of current
database if any.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}TABLE OF CONTENTS@{us}@{ub} - Go to a 'table of contents' page if
it exists for current document.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}RETRACE@{us}@{ub} - Go back one page in history list.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}BROWSE BACKWARD@{us}@{ub} - Go to the previous physical page or
to the page specified with @PREV tag.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}BROWSE FORWARD@{us}@{ub} - Go to the next physical page or
to the page specified with @NEXT tag.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}HELP@{us}@{ub} - Load the help page for this database if available.@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}ADD BOOKMARK@{us}@{ub} - Not available@{n}
@{"dot" timg}
@{b}@{s}GO TO BOOKMARKS@{us}@{ub} - Not available@{n}
@endnode

@node keyboard "Keyboard control"
@toc usage
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Keyboard control"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{font f2}NOTE: These are default settings ! You can change the keys
by editing ixg.prefs file. @{"Click here" LINK prefs#Keyboard} to see available
keywords.@{font ix}@{n}
@{"dot" timg}@{b}@{s}Document scrolling with keyboard@{us}@{ub}@{n}
@{b}CURSOR KEYS@{ub} - up/down/left/right - scroll for a small amount.
This amount can be changed in prefs file with @{"SCROLLSS" LINK prefs#SCROLLSS}
keyword.@{n}
@{b}ALT + CURSOR KEYS@{ub} - up/down/left/right - scroll for a bigger amount.
This amount can be changed in prefs file with @{"SCROLLBS" LINK prefs#SCROLLBS}
keyword.@{n}
@{b}SHIFT + CURSOR KEYS@{ub} - scroll one page up/down/left/right.@{n}
@{b}CTRL + CURSOR KEYS@{ub} - go to the extreme up/down/left/right of the document@{p}
@{"dot" timg}@{b}@{s}Panel buttons shortcuts@{us}@{ub}@{n}
@{b}RIGHT AMIGA + I@{ub} - INFO button.@{n}
@{b}RIGHT AMIGA + L@{ub} - LOAD NEW FILE button.@{n}
@{b}RIGHT AMIGA + O@{ub} - OPEN NEW WINDOW button.@{n}
@{b}i@{ub} - INDEX button.@{n}
@{b}c@{ub} - TABLE OF CONTENTS button.@{n}
@{b}r@{ub} - RETRACE button.@{n}
@{b},@{ub} - BROWSE BACKWARD button.@{n}
@{b}.@{ub} - BROWSE FORWARD button.@{n}
@{b}h@{ub} - HELP button.@{n}
@{b}RIGHT AMIGA + A@{ub} - ADD BOOKMARK button.@{n}
@{b}RIGHT AMIGA + G@{ub} - GO TO BOOKMARKS button.@{n}
@endnode

