@node 1_load "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Load..."}@{n}
@{a l dw}
This will open the file requester where you can choose the new file to load.@{p}
After you press @{b}OK@{ub}, @{_ix} will check the file format by asking
@{b}iX datatypes@{ub} (if any). If file was recognized by iX datatypes, @{_ix}
will choose the correct iX datatype to load file. It may happen that file
was recognized by more than one iX datatype. In that case, @{_ix} will ask
@{b}you@{ub} to choose the correct iX datatype to be used for file processing.@{p}
If file wasn't recognized by iX datatypes, @{_ix} will ask standard @{b}AmigaOS
datatype system@{ub} for the file type. If file type is @{b}DOCUMENT or
PICTURE or ASCII TEXT@{ub}, the file will be loaded. Otherwise, @{_ix} will
pop up the message - @{b}" File is not of required type "@{ub}.@{p}
@{_ix} will always change the current directory to the directory of
current database.
@endnode

@node 1_open "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Open..."}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 1_nextw "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Next window"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 1_prevw "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Previous window"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 1_screen "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Screen..."}@{n}
@{a l dw}
This will pop up the requester where you can choose the screen mode
and number of colors for new custom screen. If you press OK, iX-Guide
will jump to new screen.
@endnode

@node 1_defscr "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Goto Default Screen"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
This will close the custom screen and iX-Guide will jump back to
default screen.
@endnode

@node 1_about "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Info"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
This will open the @{b}about requester@{ub}. In this window you can
find some copyright information and information about current database.@{p}
@endnode

@node 1_quit "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - iX-Guide/Quit"}@{n}
@{a l dw}
This will quit @{_ix} program.
@endnode

@node 2_search "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Node/Search text..."}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 2_viewns "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Node/View node source"}@{n}
Reloads the current document but ignoring tags so you can actually see
the source of document.@{p}
@{b}NOTE:@{ub} This works only with @{b}IXML@{ub} and @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub}
documents. You can't view the source of file loaded by iX datatypes.
@endnode

@node 2_saven "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Node/Save node"}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 2_savept "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Node/Save as plain text"}@{n}
Saves the currently displayed document as @{b}plain text@{ub}.
Opens the file requester asking you for the name of destination file.
If file already exists, @{_ix} will ask you whether you want to overwrite
it or not.
@endnode

@node 2_print "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Node/Print..."}@{n}
This is actually the same as 'Save as plain text'. The only difference
is that converted document is sent to printer.
@endnode

@node 2_reload "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Node/Reload"}@{n}
Reload the current document from the disk.@{p}
@{b}NOTE:@{ub} This will reload just a document, not the images !
@endnode

@node 3_findn "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Navigation/Find node..."}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 3_addbm "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Navigation/Add bookmark"}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 3_gotobm "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Navigation/Go to bookmarks"}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 3_savebm "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Navigation/Save bookmarks"}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 3_gstruct "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Navigation/Guide Structure."}@{n}
@{b}Not yet implemented.@{ub}
@endnode

@node 4_flushd "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Images/Flush displayed images"}@{n}
This will flush all images in current document and will reload document.
These images are in chip ram.@{p}
@{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you have enabled image loading with @{b}Images/Load images@{ub},
images will be loaded again.
@endnode

@node 4_flushc "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Images/Flush cached images"}@{n}
This will flush all cached images and will reload document.
These images are in fast ram if available. All images that are loaded but
not currently displayed are in this cache.
@endnode

@node 4_flusha "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Images/Flush all images"}@{n}
This will flush all images, those currently displayed and cached.@{n}
@{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you have enabled image loading with @{b}Images/Load images@{ub},
images in the current document will be loaded again.
@endnode

@node 4_loadi "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Images/Load images"}@{n}
If @{b}checked@{ub} @{_ix} will load images, otherwise it won't.
@endnode

@node 4_drawbg "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Images/Draw background"}@{n}
If @{b}checked@{ub} @{_ix} will draw the background image if any,
otherwise it won't. This will also reload current document.
@endnode

@node 4_playa "Menus"
@toc menus
@{a l c}@{"logo" timg}@{_high "Menus - Images/Play animations"}@{n}
If @{b}checked@{ub} @{_ix} will start the animations, otherwise it will
stop the animations.
@endnode

@node arexx_demo "These are iX-Guide arexx capabilities !"
@background #bb99bb

@rexx "ixclient_1.rexx >CON:0/150/640/100/iXRexxClient1/AUTO/CLOSE"
@rexx "ixclient_2.rexx"
@rexx "ixclient_3.rexx"

@{a c dw}
@{b}@{font f4}This is demo of iX Arexx@{font ix}@{ub}@{n}
The first rectangle object is controled by ixclient_1 arexx
program and the second one is controled by ixclient_3.@{n}
You can write some text into rect 1 or place word 'Arexx' with mouse
in rect 1. You can start and stop the text scrolling
in rect 2. You can also see in the CLI events that are reported by
ixclient_1 if you press a mouse, scroll virtual gadget, press some key etc.
The third rectangle is controled by ixclient_2 and it demonstrates loading
of datatype images, changing fonts, text styles etc.@{p}
@{"START TEXT SCROLLING" LINK rx_start} @{"STOP TEXT SCROLLING" LINK rx_stop}@{n}
@{rect 250 150}     @{rect 200 120}@{n}
@{rect 300 120}
@endnode
